Package: libnginx-mod-http-soft-limit-req
Architecture: any
Depends: nginx (>> @NGINX_VERSION_LOWER@), nginx (<< @NGINX_VERSION_UPPER@), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: tag-don't-reject soft rate-limiter module for nginx
 A dynamic nginx module providing soft_limit_req: a tag-don't-reject rate
 limiter. It runs the stock limit_req leaky-bucket math but, on overflow, never
 rejects the request. Instead it writes a per-directive verdict variable
 ("1" when over the cap, "" otherwise) that a map can consume to reroute
 over-cap "grey" traffic to a separate upstream, while a stock limit_req keeps
 hard-blocking abusive clients in the same location.
 .
 Each soft_limit_req directive gets its own verdict variable and every zone is
 evaluated on every request, so a hard-rejecting zone and one or more tag-only
 zones can coexist in a single location without ever returning an error to
 legitimate under-cap users. This is the supported way to shed an L7 flood to a
 sacrificial or challenge tier without dropping organic traffic.
